{
  "info": {
    "name": "ProjectFlow API",
    "description": "# ProjectFlow — Mini Project Management System\n\nComplete API collection for the ProjectFlow backend.\n\n## Base URL\n`http://localhost:5000`\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Import this collection **and** the `ProjectFlow.postman_environment.json` environment file.\n2. Select the **ProjectFlow Local** environment from the top-right dropdown.\n3. Run the requests in order — **Create Project** and **Create Task** automatically save IDs into the environment variables `projectId` and `taskId`.\n\n## Features Covered\n- Pagination (`?page` + `?limit`)\n- Task filtering by `status`\n- Task sorting by `due_date`\n- Input validation (400 error examples included)\n- Proper error responses (404, 400, 500)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base", "value": "http://localhost:5000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "projectId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "taskId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🩺 Health Check",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Verifies the server is running. Returns `{ ok: true }`."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "url": { "raw": "{{base}}/health" }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\n  \"ok\": true\n}"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Server is healthy', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "📁 Projects",
      "description": "CRUD operations for Projects. The **Create Project** request automatically stores the returned `_id` into the `projectId` **environment** variable for use in subsequent requests.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Project",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base}}/projects",
              "host": ["{{base}}"],
              "path": ["projects"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Website Redesign\",\n  \"description\": \"Full company website overhaul with new branding and UX\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Creates a new project.\n\n**Required fields:** `name`\n\n**Optional fields:** `description`\n\nThe test script automatically saves the new project's `_id` to the `projectId` **environment** variable."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base}}/projects" },
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Website Redesign\",\n  \"description\": \"Full company website overhaul\"\n}"
                }
              },
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "body": "{\n  \"_id\": \"664f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d\",\n  \"name\": \"Website Redesign\",\n  \"description\": \"Full company website overhaul with new branding and UX\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-10T08:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"__v\": 0\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Validation Error — missing name",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
                "url": { "raw": "{{base}}/projects" },
                "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
              },
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Validation failed\",\n  \"details\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"field\",\n      \"msg\": \"Name is required\",\n      \"path\": \"name\",\n      \"location\": \"body\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 Created', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has _id, name, description, created_at', function () {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json).to.have.property('_id');",
                  "  pm.expect(json).to.have.property('name');",
                  "  pm.expect(json).to.have.property('description');",
                  "  pm.expect(json).to.have.property('created_at');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Auto-save project ID for subsequent requests",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json._id) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('projectId', json._id);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('projectId', json._id);",
                  "  console.log('✅ projectId saved:', json._id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
